### HEPEvt related ###

generate_HEPEvt.cxx:
	generate HEPEvt file of Migdal signal
	used for input of Geant4 simulation
	g++ `root-config --cflags --libs` generate_HEPEvt.cxx -o generate_HEPEvt

check_HEPEvt.C:
	checking macro of HEPEvt file

migdal_????_n???keV:
	HEPEvt file generated by generate_HEPEvt
	distribution of E_NR, E_e, E_X, ... are checked by check_HEPEvt.C

migdal_Xe1s_n565keV_q_dep_check:
	check for scaling of the probability of E_e
	proportional to q maybe same to the paper
	flag distribusion is correspond to the normal elastic scattering
	(due to flat distribution of costheta_CM)
	q^2 distribution also plotted

ibe_data:
	used for generate_HEPEvt.cxx
	probability as a functino of E_e [https://arxiv.org/src/1707.07258v3/anc]
	draw_migdal_ibe_??.C is the draw macro to check for comparing to the paper

fl_tr_pr:
	used for generate_HEPEvt.cxx
	characteristic X-ray data (copied from Geant4 library)



### other programs ###

recoil_energy:
	E_NR spectrum calculation accounting inelastic-like scattering dependence of (E_e+E_EX) assuming some cos(theta)

branching_ratio:
	show branching ratio of Migdal event for each (n,l) and for Ar/Xe

calc_prob:
	calculation of scaling of (q/511eV)^2

fiducial_efficiency:
	efficiency of containing two clusters separating some length in the 30x30x30cm3 volume

sansouken:
	neutron source reaction check
	energy and angle distributions are calculated


xenon_inelastic:
	check inelastic data in Geant4
	quick check copmmand: openssl zlib -d -in 54_129_Xenon.z
	data: /home/axel/src/20180928_ForGeant4/geant4.10.04.p02-build/data/G4NDL4.5/Inelastic/F01/54_129_Xenon.z
